 Conventions are often cultural and learned.
 Whereas they do not physically prevent an activity, they prohibit some
 activities and encourage others 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Norman1999"

\end_inset

.
 For example, in most western countries, the red color will indicate that
 an action is forbidden or not recommended as the green color will suggest
 something that is allowed.
